</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="326" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1067,2031]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1536,1562]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz, M. &amp; Bamber, R. N." box="[324,801,1536,1562]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" pagination="1 - 235" refId="ref18926" refString="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz, M. &amp; Bamber, R. N. (2012) The Shallow-water Tanaidacea (Arthropoda: Malacostraca: Peracarida) of the Bass Strait, Victoria, Australia (other than the Tanaidae). Memoirs of Museum Victoria, 69, 1 - 235. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2012.69.0 1" type="journal article" year="2012">Błażewicz-Paszkowycz &amp; Bamber (2012)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz &amp; Bamber" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[988,1123,1536,1561]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anarsios">
<emphasis box="[988,1123,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">M. anarsios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is “strange, incongruous… on a number of characters from the current diagnosis for the genus” 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sieg" authorityYear="1986" box="[914,1112,1572,1598]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Meromonakantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[914,1112,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Meromonakantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. So, this species was already problematic owing its morphological divergences, mainly by its robustly calcified body, large cephalothorax about 1.4 times L:W and not well separated pereonites and pleonites. Although the authors provisionally included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz &amp; Bamber" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anarsios">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">T. anarsios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sieg" authorityYear="1986" box="[278,476,1680,1706]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Meromonakantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,476,1680,1706]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Meromonakantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they pointed that with a high probability it represents a monotypic genus. Because the morphological differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz, 2019" authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" box="[549,706,1716,1742]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[549,706,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Targaryenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[711,815,1716,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[711,815,1716,1742]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and all other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sieg" authorityYear="1986" box="[964,1162,1716,1742]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Meromonakantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[964,1162,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Meromonakantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are apparent, we decided to erect a new genus. The list of the characters that distinguish the two genera is shown in the 
<tableCitation box="[1297,1383,1752,1778]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,239,370,394]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="TABLE 4. Differences between Meromonakantha and Targaryenella." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/1BA66669BE3D1D73FF1AFB3AA6E776D3" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" tableUuid="1BA66669BE3D1D73FF1AFB3AA6E776D3">Table 4</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1067,2031]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">
With a three-articled antennule, no eyes and non-serrate incisor of the mandible, the new genus is classified to the family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sieg" authorityYear="1984" box="[271,447,1824,1850]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Typhlotanaidae</taxonomicName>
. The absence of the ‘prickly tubercles’ (= clinging apparatus) on pereopods 4–6 excludes it from a large group of typhlotanaids e.g. 
<emphasis box="[634,1086,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" authorityYear="2007" box="[634,797,1860,1885]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Larsenotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Larsenotanais</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" authorityYear="2007" box="[809,930,1860,1886]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Typhlamia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G.O.Sars" authorityYear="1882" box="[942,1086,1860,1886]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Typhlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Typhlotanais</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" authorityYear="2007" box="[1125,1232,1860,1886]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Torquella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1125,1232,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Torquella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Błażewicz-Pasz- kowycz 2007; Błażewicz &amp; Bamber 2012). With walking-type pereopods 4–6, 
<taxonomicName authority="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz, 2019" authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" box="[1073,1230,1896,1922]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1073,1230,1896,1922]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Targaryenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to four typhlotanaid genera— 
<emphasis box="[401,850,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segadilha, Gellert &amp; Blazewicz" authorityYear="2018" box="[401,488,1932,1958]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Aremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aremus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" authorityYear="2007" box="[499,640,1932,1958]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Hamatipeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hamatipeda</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sieg" authorityYear="1986" box="[652,850,1932,1958]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Meromonakantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Meromonakantha</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Segadilha et al. 2018)" authorityName="Segadilha" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Segadilha" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[904,1364,1932,1958]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Paratyphlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[904,1098,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Paratyphlotanais</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Segadilha, J. L. &amp; Gellert, M. &amp; Blazewicz, M." box="[1113,1356,1932,1958]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" pagination="915 - 925" refId="ref19961" refString="Segadilha, J. L., Gellert, M. &amp; Blazewicz, M. (2018) A new genus of Tanaidacea (Peracarida, Typhlotanaidae) from the Atlantic slope. Marine Biodiversity, 48, 915 - 925. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 018 - 0856 - y" type="journal article" year="2018">
Segadilha 
<emphasis box="[1232,1282,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1067,2031]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,153,323]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="326" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">
The presence of the well-developed pleopods distinguishes 
<taxonomicName authority="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz, 2019" authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" box="[866,1023,1968,1994]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[866,1023,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Targaryenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segadilha, Gellert &amp; Blazewicz" authorityYear="2018" box="[1091,1176,1968,1994]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Aremus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1091,1176,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">Aremus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has pleopods fully reduced (
<bibRefCitation author="Segadilha, J. L. &amp; Gellert, M. &amp; Blazewicz, M." box="[254,495,2004,2030]" pageId="16" pageNumber="325" pagination="915 - 925" refId="ref19961" refString="Segadilha, J. L., Gellert, M. &amp; Blazewicz, M. (2018) A new genus of Tanaidacea (Peracarida, Typhlotanaidae) from the Atlantic slope. Marine Biodiversity, 48, 915 - 925. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 018 - 0856 - y" type="journal article" year="2018">
Segadilha 
<emphasis box="[373,422,2004,2030]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="325">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), while its regular (gently rounded) cephalothorax allows it to be distinguished from members of 
<taxonomicName box="[294,488,153,179]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Paratyphlotanais" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,488,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="326">Paratyphlotanais</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where the cephalothorax is generally conical (
<bibRefCitation author="Bird, G. J." box="[1025,1146,153,179]" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" pagination="1359 - 1384" refId="ref18781" refString="Bird, G. J. (2004) The Tanaidacea (Crustacea, Peracarida) of the North-East Atlantic: The shelf and bathyal Paratyphlotanais of the ' Atlantic Margin. ' Journal of Natural History, 38, 1359 - 1384. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 0022293031000155359" type="journal article" year="2004">Bird 2004</bibRefCitation>
). A long dactylus and unguis combined (claw) in the pereopods 1–3 (at least as long as propodus) and simple unguis in the pereopods 4–6, distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz, 2019" authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" box="[283,440,225,251]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[283,440,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="326">Targaryenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" authorityYear="2007" box="[510,648,225,251]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Hamatipeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[510,648,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="326">Hamatipeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has the pereopods 1–3 claw shorter than the propodus and has a trifurcate tip on the unguis of pereopods 4–6. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz" authorityYear="2007" box="[793,931,261,287]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Hamatipeda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,931,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="326">Hamatipeda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has robust hook-like spines on the carpus of pereopods 4–6 (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz, M." box="[379,710,297,323]" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" pagination="1 - 141" refId="ref18876" refString="Blazewicz-Paszkowycz, M. (2007) A revision of the family Typhlotanaidae Sieg 1984 (Crustacea: Tanaidacea) with the remarks on the Nototanaidae Sieg, 1976. Zootaxa, 1598, 1 - 141. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1598.1.1" type="journal article" year="2007">Błażewicz-Paszkowycz 2007</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName authority="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz, 2019" authorityName="Segadilha &amp; Serejo &amp; Błażewicz" authorityYear="2019" box="[799,956,297,323]" class="Malacostraca" family="Typhlotanaidae" genus="Targaryenella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tanaidacea" pageId="17" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[799,956,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="326">Targaryenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has regular spines at these loci.
</paragraph>
